INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '968daa66-d610-45e4-9619-6b71e5bb6908',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$ollama + LangChain LCEL — Chains, Tools, and Agents on Local Models$escape$,
  $escape$LangChain's LCEL pipe operator works directly with `ChatOllama` from `langchain_ollama`. Swap out `ChatOpenAI` and your chain runs entirely local — same syntax, zero API calls.

For tool use, only certain Ollama models support function calling: `llama3.1`, `mistral-nemo`, and `qwen2.5` are reliable picks. Run `ollama show llama3.1 --modelfile` and check for the `tools` template block — if it's absent, `.bind_tools()` will silently produce no tool calls.

Memory integrates via `RunnableWithMessageHistory`. Wrap your LCEL chain, supply a `get_session_history` callback, and LangChain injects prior turns into the prompt before each `ChatOllama` inference. Everything stays on-device.

For agents, `create_tool_calling_agent` paired with `AgentExecutor` handles the reasoning loop. `ChatOllama` streams tokens back; LangChain parses tool call JSON, dispatches, and reinjects observations. Set `streaming=True` on `ChatOllama` so long agent traces don't block the thread. Avoid `llama3.2:1b` for agents — smaller quantized models struggle to produce valid tool-call JSON consistently; use at least the 8B variant.$escape$,
  $escape$from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama
from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate
from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser
from langchain_core.tools import tool

@tool
def word_count(text: str) -> int:
    """Return the number of words in the given text."""
    return len(text.split())

llm = ChatOllama(model="llama3.1", temperature=0)  # needs tool-calling support
llm_with_tools = llm.bind_tools([word_count])

prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([
    ("system", "Use tools when appropriate."),
    ("human", "{input}"),
])

chain = prompt | llm_with_tools
result = chain.invoke({"input": "How many words in: the quick brown fox jumps?"})
print(result.tool_calls)  # [{'name': 'word_count', 'args': {'text': '...'}, ...}]$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
